<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'> Positive Numbers </h3>
</div>
<p>
In <strong>number line</strong> moving towards right means <strong>positive numbers (i.e. from zero (0), upward).</strong> 
<br>
<strong>Positive numbers</strong> are numbers greater than zero; they have positive symbol (+) preceding 
the numbers e.g. +5, +6, +1 etc. 
Sometimes, not always written with the positive symbol (+) i.e. +5 => 5
</p>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'> Negative Numbers </h3>
</div>
<p>
In <strong>number line</strong> moving towards left means <strong>negative numbers (i.e. from zero (0), downward).</strong>
<br> 
<strong>Negative numbers</strong> are number less than zero (0). They usually have negative symbol (-) preceding the numbers e.g. -2, -3, -14 etc.  
</p>

<p>
 Note; <strong>Zero</strong> is a number that is neither <strong> positive </strong> nor <strong>negative.</strong>
</p>

<br>
<div class="container">
