   <strong>Example 1 </strong> 
<br>                        
A monkey is sitting at the top of a mango tree which is 8m above the surface of the river. A frog swims 4m below the surface of the river. Find (i) the position of the monkey and the frog as distance from the river surface (ii) How far is the frog below the monkey?
<br>  
<strong>Solution</strong>
<br>  	
<strong>Above</strong> means <strong>positive(+)</strong> and <strong>Below</strong> means <strong>negative(-)</strong>
<br>  
(i)	
<br>  
The position of the <strong>monkey</strong> to the river surface = <strong> +8m </strong>
<br>  
The position of the <strong>frog</strong> to the river surface = <strong>-4m</strong>
<br>  
(ii)
<br>  
<strong>Frog</strong> below the <strong>monkey</strong> distance = +8m – (-4m) 
<br>
<strong>Distance</strong> = 8m + 4m = <strong>12m</strong>
   </div>
   <div class="col">
   <strong>Example 2</strong>
   <br>
   A lady arrives at the meeting 15minutes early. A man is 5minutes late. How long has the lady been waiting in the meeting room before the man arrived?
   <br>
   <strong>Solution </strong>
   <br>
   <strong>Before</strong> means positive (+) and <strong>After</strong> means negative (-) 
   <br>
   The lady’s time =  <strong> +15 minutes  </strong>
   <br>
   The man’s time =  <strong>-5 minutes </strong>
   <br>
   The lady’s waiting period = +15 – (-5) 
   <br>
   The lady’s waiting period = 15 + 5 
   <br>
   The lady’s waiting period = <strong>20minutes</strong>
