 <div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
 <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Addition of Positive Numbers</h3>
 </div>
 <p>
 In this section, for easy understanding, look at the positive (+) as what you have with you and the negative (-) as what you are going to give out (debt).
 </p>
 <br>
 <div class="container-fluid">
 <div class="row">
   <div class="col border-right border-danger">
   <strong>Example 1</strong>
   <br>
   Simplify 3 + 5 
   <br>
   <strong>Solution</strong>
   <br>
   3 + 5 = (+3) + (+5) = <b>+8</b>
   <br>
   <strong>The above means you have 3 and 5 (i.e. +3 and +5), you have total of 8 with you (i.e. +8)</strong>
   
   </div>
   <div class="col">
   <strong>Example 2</strong>
   <br>
   Simplify 6 + (-12)
   <br>
   <strong>Solution</strong>
   <br>
   6 + (-12) = (+6) + (-12) = -6
   <br>
   <strong>The above means you have 6 (i.e. +6), you owe 12 (i.e. -12) 
   if you give out the 6 you have with you, and you still have 6 to balance up (i.e. - 6).</strong>
  
   </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
 <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Subtraction of the Positive Number</h3>
 </div>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
    <br>
    Simplify +6 – (+4)
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong>
    <br>
    <strong>Note:  - x + = - (i.e. product of Positive sign (+) and Negative sign (-) gives Negative result)</strong>
    <br>
    +6 – (+4) = +6 – 4 = <strong>+2</strong>
    <br>
    <strong>The above means you have 6 (i.e. +6) and owe 4 (i.e. -4), if you pay the 4, you will still have 2 with you (i.e. +2).</strong> 
    <br>
    <br>
    <strong>Example 2</strong>
    <br>
    Solve +4 – (+9)
    <br>
    <strong>Solution</strong>
    <br>
    Note:  - x + = -
    <br>
    +4 – (+9) = +4 – 9 = <strong>-5</strong>
    <br>
    <strong>The above means you have 4 (i.e. +4), owe 9 (i.e. -9), if you give out the 
    4 you will still have 5 (i.e. -5) to balance up.</strong>
   
  

