      <strong>Example 2</strong>
      <br>
      Simplify (-2) + (-4)
      <br>
     <strong> Solution</strong>
     <br>
     <strong>Note:  + x - = - </strong>
     <br>
      (-2) + (-4) = -2 – 4 = -6
      <br>
      <strong>The above means you owe 2 (i.e. -2), you owe 4 as well (i.e. -4), in total you owe 6 (i.e. -2 and -4).</strong>
      
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
