     <br>
     <strong>Solution</strong>
     <br>
     3 + 5 = (+3) + (+5) = <b>+8</b>
     <br>
     <strong>The above means you have 3 and 5 (i.e. +3 and +5), you have total of 8 with you (i.e. +8)</strong>
     
     </div>
     <div class="col">
     <strong>Example 2</strong>
     <br>
     Simplify 6 + (-12)
     <br>
     <strong>Solution</strong>
     <br>
     6 + (-12) = (+6) + (-12) = -6
     <br>
     <strong>The above means you have 6 (i.e. +6), you owe 12 (i.e. -12) 
     if you give out the 6 you have with you, and you still have 6 to balance up (i.e. - 6).</strong>
    
     </div>
