      <br>
      Simplify +6 – (+4)
      <br>
      <strong>Solution</strong>
      <br>
      <strong>Note:  - x + = - (i.e. product of Positive sign (+) and Negative sign (-) gives Negative result)</strong>
      <br>
      +6 – (+4) = +6 – 4 = <strong>+2</strong>
      <br>
      <strong>The above means you have 6 (i.e. +6) and owe 4 (i.e. -4), if you pay the 4, you will still have 2 with you (i.e. +2).</strong> 
